    {
      "step": 1,
      "text": "A linear function with slope 2 has the form $g(x) = 2x + b$."
    },
    {
      "step": 2,
      "text": "Substitute the point $(1, 14)$: $14 = 2(1) + b \\Rightarrow b = 12$. So $g(x) = 2x + 12$."
    },
    {
      "step": 3,
      "text": "Evaluate each choice.",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": "A",
          "explanation": "<ul><li>$g(x) = 2x$ has $b=0$. Checking: $g(1) = 2(1) = 2 \\neq 14$. Not correct.</li></ul>"
        },
        {
          "id": "B",
          "explanation": "<ul><li>$g(x) = 2x+2$ gives $g(1) = 4 \\neq 14$. Not correct.</li></ul>"
        },
        {
          "id": "C",
          "explanation": "<ul><li>$g(x) = 2x+12$ gives $g(1) = 2+12 = 14$ ✓ and slope $= 2$ ✓. That matches choice C &mdash; <strong>C</strong> is correct.</li></ul>"
        },
        {
          "id": "D",
          "explanation": "<ul><li>$g(x) = 2x+14$ gives $g(1) = 16 \\neq 14$. Not correct.</li></ul>"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
